{
  "text": "Ellipsoidal uncertainty set (UE) [CITATION_1] [17] [CITATION_2] is widely used to model parameter uncertainty, by using the maximal inscribed ellipsoid inside the variation region. For any vector n X R \u2208 with random perturbation around its nominal value 0 X , the parameter variability can be estimated by an uncertainty ellipsoid in n R , which has the form [CITATION_3] :",
